com.escape.games.view
Class HostSupport

java.lang.Object
  com.escape.games.view.HostSupport

public class HostSupport
extends java.lang.Object

Utility methods for host application support. Invoke-safe means the method may be called from any thread, because the method posts a Runnable to the view or calls Activity.runOnUiThread() to perform the operation.

Author:
escape-llc

animTextAt

public static java.lang.Runnable animTextAt(android.view.LayoutInflater li,
                                            android.view.ViewGroup root,
                                            int x,
                                            int y,
                                            int layout,
                                            int color,
                                            java.lang.CharSequence text,
                                            int resid)
Bind a runnable to animate display of text at given location. A new layout is created to contain the text.

Parameters:
li - Layout inflater.
root - View to add the animated text into. Should be RelativeLayout.
x - x location
y - y location
layout - layout resource id. Must be TextView.
color - text color. Pass Color.TRANSPARENT to use the layout's value.
text - text to display
resid - animation resource id
Returns:
new instance bound to parameters.

enableUi

public static void enableUi(android.app.Fragment fx,
                            int vid,
                            int animin,
                            int animout,
                            boolean enabled)
Invoke-safe perform animation on fragment's view according to enabled flag. If anything in the chain Fragment->Activity->View is NULL, nothing occurs.

Parameters:
fx - Fragment must be !NULL.
vid - View id.
animin - Animation for enabled.
animout - Animation for !enabled.
enabled - Enabled flag.
